Consulate of the United States of America at Sierra Leone
23rd May 1864

No.7
Sir,
I have the pleasure to forward the Department of State, per British ferg "Emma" a package of the "Bean of Calabar", about 10 lbs, which I obtained hrough the kindness f the Rev. A. Robb at Calabar, whose letter I enclose, should more be required I can obtain them from the source source You

Hon. J.N. Seward
Secretary of State
Washington

you will notice the article cort 6/ per lb., sterling, which is, here, $1.44, there had been about 50 cents expense on them. 

I have the honor to be 
Sir
Your obdt Servant
Henry Rider
U.S. Consular gent 
